Step 1: Update System Packages
Before installing any new software, refresh your local package index and upgrade existing packages.

sudo apt update
sudo apt upgrade -y

Step 2: Download Webmin Package
Download the latest Debian package (.deb) directly from the official Webmin server.

wget http://www.webmin.com/download/deb/webmin-current.deb

Step 3: Install Webmin & Fix Dependencies
Use dpkg to start the installation. If there are missing dependencies, apt -f will automatically detect and install them.

sudo dpkg -i webmin-current.deb
sudo apt -f install -y

Step 4: Verify Service Status
Check if the Webmin service is active and running correctly.

sudo systemctl status webmin

Step 5: Configure Login Credentials
Set or change the password for your Webmin user (e.g., admin or root) to ensure you can log in via the web interface.

sudo /usr/share/webmin/changepass.pl /etc/webmin <username> <password>

Step 6: Configure Firewall (UFW)
Webmin communicates over port 10000. You must allow this port through your firewall to access the dashboard.

sudo ufw allow 10000/tcp
sudo ufw enable
sudo ufw status

How to Access Webmin

Once the installation is complete, open your web browser and navigate to:
https://your-server-ip(public):10000

Note: Since Webmin uses a self-signed SSL certificate by default, your browser might show a security warning. You can safely proceed to the site.
